{
  "Though this equation gives us a simple mental model for how React works, there's one aspect of the equation that still, after all these years, seems to confuse people. Exactly <em metastring=\"\">when</em> and <em metastring=\"\">how</em> is <code>f</code> invoked? Or said differently, <span class=\"font-black tracking-wider\" style=\"color:var(--beige)\">exactly <em metastring=\"\">when</em> and <em metastring=\"\">how</em> does React update the view?</span>": "这个等式给了我们理解 React 工作方式的一个简单心智模型，但其中有一部分多年来仍让人困惑：<code>f</code> 到底<em metastring=\"\">什么时候</em>、<em metastring=\"\">怎么</em>被调用？换句话说，<span class=\"font-black tracking-wider\" style=\"color:var(--beige)\">React 到底<em metastring=\"\">什么时候</em>以及<em metastring=\"\">怎样</em>更新视图？</span>",
  "To better answer this, instead of starting with <em metastring=\"\">how</em> or <em metastring=\"\">when</em>, let's go back one step further and start from first principles. First, <em metastring=\"\">what</em> is <span class=\"sparkle_wrapper__cL2jQ\"><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:45%;left:11%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"19\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"19\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:45%;left:1%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"12\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"12\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><strong class=\"sparkle_child_wrapper__bem0y\">rendering</strong></span>?": "为了更好地回答这个问题，我们不从<em metastring=\"\">怎么</em>或<em metastring=\"\">什么时候</em>入手，而是再退一步，从第一性原理讲起。首先，<em metastring=\"\">什么</em>是<span class=\"sparkle_wrapper__cL2jQ\"><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:45%;left:11%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"19\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"19\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:45%;left:1%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"12\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"12\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><strong class=\"sparkle_child_wrapper__bem0y\">渲染</strong></span>？",
  "That naturally leads us to our next question, <em metastring=\"\">when</em> exactly does React re-render a component?": "这自然引出了下一个问题：React 到底<em metastring=\"\">什么时候</em>会重新渲染一个 component？",
  "With that, we now have our final <button aria-controls=\"radix-:rij:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>interrogative</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>, <em metastring=\"\">how</em> does React actually know when the state of a component has changed? At this point it's fairly trivial and, once again, it has to do with our snapshot.": "由此，我们终于来到最后一个<button aria-controls=\"radix-:rij:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>疑问词</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>：React 到底<em metastring=\"\">怎样</em>知道 component 的 state 变了？到这里这个问题已经相当简单，它又一次和我们前面说的 snapshot 有关。",
  "From there, if the event handler contains an invocation of <code>useState</code>'s updater function <strong metastring=\"\">and</strong> React sees that the new state is different than the state in the snapshot, React will trigger a re-render of the component – creating a new snapshot and updating the view.": "接下来，如果事件处理函数里包含对 <code>useState</code> 更新函数的调用，<strong metastring=\"\">并且</strong> React 发现新 state 和 snapshot 里的 state 不同，React 就会触发该 component 的重新渲染 —— 生成一个新的 snapshot，并更新视图。",
  "Again, React will only re-render if the event handler contains an invocation of <code>useState</code>'s updater function (✅) <strong metastring=\"\">and</strong> React sees that the new state is different than the state in the snapshot (❌).": "再强调一次：React 只有在事件处理函数里调用了 <code>useState</code> 的更新函数（✅），<strong metastring=\"\">且</strong> React 发现新 state 和 snapshot 里的 state 不同（❌）时，才会重新渲染。",
  "Instead, React will only re-render after it's taken into account every updater function inside of the event handler and it's sure what the final state is. So in our example, React will only re-render <strong metastring=\"\">once</strong> per click.": "React 只会在把事件处理函数里的所有更新函数都处理完、确定最终的 state 之后，才触发一次重新渲染。所以在我们的例子里，每次点击 React 只会<strong metastring=\"\">渲染一次</strong>。",
  "Very welcoming. Notice anything peculiar about how our app works, though? Before you play with it, try to guess <em metastring=\"\">when</em> our nested <code>Wave</code> component will re-render.": "挺热情的一个例子。不过你有没有注意到它有个地方挺怪？先别急着玩，试着猜一下：嵌套在里面的 <code>Wave</code> component 会在<em metastring=\"\">什么时候</em>重新渲染？",
  "Your intuition is probably thinking <strong metastring=\"\">never</strong>. After all, if React truly only re-renders when it absolutely has to, why would <code>Wave</code> ever re-render since it doesn't accept any props and has no state?": "你的直觉多半是“<strong metastring=\"\">永远不会</strong>”。毕竟，如果 React 真的只在绝对必要时才重新渲染，<code>Wave</code> 既没有 props 也没有 state，凭什么会重新渲染？",
  "Notice that <code>Wave</code> re-renders whenever we click the <code>button</code> (changing the <code>index</code> state inside of <code>Greeting</code>). This may not be intuitive, but it demonstrates an important aspect of React. Whenever state changes, React will re-render the component that owns that state <strong metastring=\"\">and</strong> all of its child components – regardless of whether or not those child components accept any props.": "注意，每次我们点击 <code>button</code>（改变 <code>Greeting</code> 内部的 <code>index</code> state）时，<code>Wave</code> 都会重新渲染。这可能不太直观，但它说明了 React 的一条重要规则：每当 state 变化时，React 会重新渲染拥有这块 state 的组件，<strong metastring=\"\">以及</strong>它的所有子组件 —— 无论那些子组件是否接收 props。",
  "Second, the assumption that React should only re-render child components if their props change works in a world where React components are <em metastring=\"\">always</em> pure functions and props are the only thing these components need to render. The problem, as anyone who has built a real world React app knows, is that isn't <em metastring=\"\">always</em> the case.": "第二，“只有 props 变化时才重新渲染子组件”这个假设，只有在组件<em metastring=\"\">始终</em>是纯函数、且 props 是组件渲染所需的唯一输入时才成立。而任何写过真实 React 项目的人都知道，<em metastring=\"\">并非</em>总是这样。",
  "Third, if you do have an expensive component and you want that component to opt out of this default behavior and <em metastring=\"\">only</em> re-render when its props change, you can use React's <code>React.memo</code> higher-order component.": "第三，如果你确实有个开销很大的组件，并且希望它退出这种默认行为、<em metastring=\"\">仅</em>在 props 变化时才重新渲染，可以使用 React 的高阶组件 <code>React.memo</code>。",
  "That's an exaggeration, but it does change things just a <em metastring=\"\">little</em> bit.": "虽然说得夸张了点，但它确实<em metastring=\"\">稍微</em>改变了一些事情。",
  "All our examples until this point have had strict mode <strong metastring=\"\">disabled</strong>, for obvious reasons. But so you can see it in action, here's our <code>Wave</code> example now in <code>StrictMode</code>.": "到目前为止，我们所有的例子都<strong metastring=\"\">关闭</strong>了严格模式，原因显而易见。不过为了让你看看效果，下面是放进 <code>StrictMode</code> 里的 <code>Wave</code> 例子。",
  "Notice that every time we click the button, our app renders <strong metastring=\"\">twice</strong>.": "注意，每次我们点击按钮，应用都会渲染<strong metastring=\"\">两次</strong>。",
  "Your intuition might be that React will re-render for every <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">updater</span> function it encounters, so 3 times in our example.": "你的直觉可能是：React 会为它遇到的每一个 <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">updater</span> 函数都重新渲染一次 —— 所以这个例子里会渲染 3 次。",
  "Now it's uncommon, but there is a way to tell React to use the value of the previous invocation of the updater function instead of replacing it. To do that, you pass the updater function a function itself that will take in the <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">value</span> from the most recent invocation as its <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">argument</span>.": "虽然不常见，但确实有办法让 React 使用上一次更新函数调用的值，而不是直接替换掉。做法是：给 updater 函数传一个函数，这个函数会把最近一次调用的 <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">值</span>作为它的 <span class=\"highlight-trigger font-medium underline decoration-brand-blue !cursor-help\" style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\">参数</span>。",
  "Are you having <button aria-controls=\"radix-:ril:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>fun</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button> yet? Let's look at another example.": "<button aria-controls=\"radix-:ril:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>玩得还开心吗</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>？我们再看一个例子。"
